{
  "text": "In previous years, biological control has been proven to be a viable management option for CRRD. Pseudomonas aeruginosa PNA1, isolated from the chickpea rhizosphere in India [CITATION_1] , was shown to efficiently suppress cocoyam root rot by the production of the antibiotics phenazine-1-carboxylic acid (PCA) and phenazine-1-carboxamide (PCN; [CITATION_2] . Moreover, phenazines and rhamnolipid-biosurfactants, produced by P. aeruginosa PNA1, were shown to act synergistically in the control of Pythium root rot on cocoyams [CITATION_3] .",
